Diehl Metering is pleased to announce its new product for the African market, the DN25 a single-jet meter. Feedback on the AURIGA DN15 and DN20 meters, in Africa in particular, regarding numerous installation constraints, difficult weather conditions and a high rate of fraud, enabled the development of this new meter with a medium diameter. A true concentration of technology and performance, Diehl Metering says AURIGA DN25 is the very best product on the single-jet meter market. Also read: Zimbabwe orders installation of Pre-Paid Water Meters The water meter is approved R=160, according to the Measuring Instruments Directive. Its main features include a rotating register, available in glass or plastic, and it is fitted with an anti-mist system for optimum reading in all environments. The body of the meter also features an anti-fraud clamp that makes it possible to prevent any damage to the grey ring. It is the first meter of the AURIGA 25-40 series. Also read: Harare to receive US $15m in Water Meters Being modular, AURIGA can be fitted with IZAR radio with OMS protocol (Open Metering System), IZAR DOSING device or an IZAR PULSE transmitter, gateway to other systems. It is also possible to use AURIGA DN25 with radio communication into a Walk-by, Drive-by or Fixed Network, and is an automatic meter reading solution by Diehl Metering. About Diehl Metering Diehl Metering companies employ around 1,800 people. They support multi-utility, industry as well as water and energy suppliers for responsible management of natural resources. From smart meters to systems solutions and software, for each challenge, Diehl Metering offers you tailor-made solutions. Globally, around 7 million meters and 5 million radio modules are produced in-house every year.